27W.F.summary: PowerCell Sweden AB (publ) develops and produces fuel cells and fuel cell systems for automotive, marine, and stationary applications in Sweden and internationally. It offers PowerCell S2 based solutions that comprise PowerCell MS-30, a fuel cell system for battery-operated electric vehicles; PowerCell PS-5, a fuel cell system that is used for electricity generation, as well as an auxiliary power generator for telecom, traffic, building, and household applications; and PowerCell S2 fuel cell stack. The company also offers PowerCell S3 based solutions, including Powercell MS-100 for heavy-duty use applications; PowerCell megawatt solutions for marine and stationary applications; and PowerCell S3 fuel cell stack for stationary and mobile applications. In addition, it offers engineering services and zero emission solutions. PowerCell Sweden AB (publ) was founded in 2008 and is based in Gothenburg, Sweden.

2F0.F.summary: AB Fagerhult, together with its subsidiaries, designs, develops, manufactures, and markets professional lighting systems for public environments. The company offers indoor and outdoor lighting products, including pendant, linear systems, recessed luminaries, surface mounted, downlight, wall and robust luminaries, decorative and integrated luminaries, spotlight, track systems, catenary and post luminaries, floodlight, bollard, recessed ground luminaries, medical supply units, emergency lighting, and system components lighting control. Its products are used in offices, retail stores, educations, healthcare, fashion and grocery shops, hotels and restaurants, park and city center, roads, residence, sports, industrial, and other applications. The company markets its products under 12 brand names, including ateljÃ© Lyktan, iGuzzini, LED LNEAR, WE-EF, FAGERHULT, LTS, aRLIGHT, eaglelighting, Whitecroft lighting, designplan LIGHTING, i VALO, and VEKO LIGHTSYSTEMS. It operates in Europe, the United Kingdom, Ireland, Australia, Finland, the United States, Africa, Italy, Netherlands, France, Spain, and internationally. The company was formerly known as Fagerhults Elektriska and changed its name to AB Fagerhult in 1974. AB Fagerhult was founded in 1945 and is headquartered in Habo, Sweden.

AQ.ST.summary: AQ Group AB (publ) manufactures and sells components and systems for industrial customers worldwide. It operates through two segments, Component and System. The company provides electric cabinets for the food industry, automatic teller machines, control and power equipment for ship cranes, control equipment for automated handling of goods in harbors, and control systems for motors and generators; and wiring harness systems and electromechanical modules to automotive, commercial vehicle, railway, and engineering industries. It also offers thermoplastic components for automotive, medical, and engineering industries; and contract manufacturing services for sheet metal components and sheet metal assemblies for automotive, telecommunication, railway, and electromechanical industries. In addition, the company provides machines and automatic equipment, including ticket machines for parking lots and travel tickets, automatic teller machines, packaging machines, and printers and passport automation systems; and transformers and inductors for use in various applications comprising motor drives, high-speed trains, solar and wind energy, marine and offshore, relay protection systems, military equipment, airplanes, and equipment for process automation. Further, it offers system solutions for the automotive industry; and mechanical engineering services for sheet metal and plastic designs. FERRO.ST.summary: Ferroamp Elektronik AB (publ) provides energy and power optimization solutions for homes, real estate, and industries in Sweden. The company offers EnergyHub, a hub that communicates with components, gathers relevant information, and optimizes the energy flow between solar panels, energy storage, electricity grid, and consumers; solar string optimizers; energy storage solutions; and Fireman Switch, a fire fighter breaker systems. It also provides technologies and systems, including adaptive current equalization (ACE) technology; Powershare; and Energy Cloud, a software portal for effect optimization with property surveillance, analytics tools, and management systems. The company was founded in 2010 and is based in SpÃ¥nga, Sweden.

H00.F.summary: Heliospectra AB (publ) provides light control systems and related services for greenhouse and controlled plant growth environments worldwide. It offers MITRA, a modular solution for indoor and greenhouse; Elixia luminaires; Siera, a vertical farming solution for predictable and repeatable results; and DYNA, a programmable LED plant lighting system. The company also offers helioCARE services comprising light planning, on site, trials, and cultivation training services. Heliospectra AB (publ) was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Gothenburg, Sweden.
